      • knownPII

        protected java.util.Set<java.lang.String> knownPII
        A set of known PII. These can be used as features when doing non-PII classification, or these can simply be PII that do not require classification and can be found via string matching instead. Defaults to an empty set.

                 Util util,
                 DPIInterface dpiInterface,
                 java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> knownPII)
        Constructor: Loads all models for the given class name, from files into local variables to be used during prediction
        Parameters:
        className - the name of the model to load (e.g. J48.class.toString().substring(6))
        util - utility object
        dpiInterface - which implementation of DPIInterface is to be used for searching packets for features

      • getClassifierFeatures

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> getClassifierFeatures(java.lang.String classifier)
        Convenience method for retrieving features associated with a particular classifier
        Parameters:
        classifier - the classifier whose features to retrieve
        Returns:
        features associated with a particular classifier if a model for it exists; otherwise general classifier features are returned, if one exists; otherwise an empty HashMap is returned.

      • getClassifierModel

        public java.lang.Object getClassifierModel(java.lang.String classifierName)
        Convenience method for retrieving a specific classifier model
        Parameters:
        classifierName - the name of the classifier to retrieve
        Returns:
        the model associated with the specified classifier (usually a Classifier or a MultiLabelLearnerBase. If there is no model for the given classifier, the general classifier model is returned. If there is no general classifier model, null is returned.

      • getClassifierInstances

        public weka.core.Instances getClassifierInstances(java.lang.String classifierName)
        Convenience method for retrieving Instances belonging to a specific classifier
        Parameters:
        classifierName - the name of the classifier whose structure to retrieve
        Returns:
        the structure associated with the specified classifier. If there is no structure for the given classifier, the general classifier structure is returned. If there is no general classifier structure, null is returned.

      • loadDomainModel

        protected abstract void loadDomainModel(java.lang.String pathToModel,
                                        java.lang.String domainOS)
                                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Loads the given model based on the type of predictor/classifier is selected upon initialization
        Parameters:
        pathToModel - path to the model file
        domainOS - the domain (TLD) and operating system to which this model should be mapped for future uses (see domainOSModel)
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if an error occurred while trying to read the model
